<item>
            <title>[SOLR-589] DisMaxRequestHandler crashes on badly formed query strings ( combinations of &quot;-&quot; and &quot;+&quot; )</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-589</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The DisMaxRequestHandler parser crashes on strings which contain double dashes or various combinations of - and + like:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;chocolate cookie -&lt;br/&gt;
chocolate -+cookie&lt;br/&gt;
chocolate --cookie&lt;br/&gt;
chocolate - - cookie&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Originally found by me:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/lucene-solr-user/200806.mbox/browser&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/lucene-solr-user/200806.mbox/browser&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And verified by Sean Tim:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/lucene-solr-user/200806.mbox/browser&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/lucene-solr-user/200806.mbox/browser&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;all platforms&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
